        "action": "Make standard code of practice for safety in soft play & indoor play mandatory",
        "additional_details": "There are many cases that have been reported in the news of incidents at soft play, which include:\r\nAccidents:\r\nhttps://www.netmums.com/coffeehouse/being-mum-794/children-4-11-years-60/759544-soft-play-centres-accidents.html\r\nBullying & Harm:\r\nhttps://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/whats-on/family-kids/mum-bullied-abused-playcentre-having-2029547\r\nFood Hygeine\r\nhttps://www.gazettelive.co.uk/news/teesside-news/investigation-play-factory-vomiting-outbreak-14443979",
        "background": "As a parent of 3 children,I know just how popular soft play centres can be for families. With UK weather, they are often needed as fair weather place for children to play. Just as the amount of centres in the UK increase, so do the amount of incidents including harm to children. Regulation is needed",
